      <akn:section eId="sec_1_301_86a">
        <akn:num>1-301.86a</akn:num>
        <akn:heading>Contingency fee contracts.</akn:heading>
<akn:subsection eId="subsec_1-301_86a_a">
      <akn:num>(a)</akn:num>
      <akn:content><akn:p></akn:p></akn:content>
    </akn:subsection><akn:subsection eId="subsec_1-301_86a_b">
      <akn:num>(b)</akn:num>
      <akn:content><akn:p>Notwithstanding any provision of federal or District of Columbia law, a contract entered into by the District of Columbia pursuant to this section may provide that costs, expenses, and fees that the private counsel charges for legal services are payable from the amount recovered. In such circumstances, the costs, expenses, and fees need not be included in an amount provided in an appropriations law.</akn:p></akn:content>
    </akn:subsection>
